                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@DuncanC Well, there are methods that yield exact decimal values -- for addition and subtraction. For division, multiplication, etc. they have the same issues as binary methods. That&apos;s why BCD is used in accounting since that deals mostly with plus and minus and you can&apos;t account for anything smaller than a penny. However something simple like &lt;code&gt;1/3*3 == 1&lt;/code&gt; fails (evaluates to false) in BCD math, just like it would fail if you used decimal division on paper.&lt;/span&gt;

