            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@DuncanC: &lt;i&gt;&quot;BCD is a lot slower than binary floating point, period.&quot;&lt;/i&gt; - Uhm, yeah. Unless it isn&apos;t. Pretty sure there are &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HP_Saturn&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;architectures&lt;/a&gt;, where BCD math is at least as fast (or faster) than IEEE-754 floating point math. But that&apos;s besides the point: If you need decimal accuracy, you cannot use IEEE-754 floating point representation. Doing so will achieve one thing only: Calculating the wrong results faster.&lt;/span&gt;

